snippet: Nneka Ogwumike scored 18 points to lead the United States to a 119-44 rout in Istanbul, with the 75-point margin of victory setting a record.
abstract: United States women's basketball team beats Angola, 119-44.
lead_paragraph: Nneka Ogwumike scored 18 points to lead the United States to a 119-44 rout in Istanbul, with the 75-point margin of victory setting a record.

headline.main: U.S. Women Trounce Angolans in Basketball World Championships
